{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Sniffles2 employs a three-phase clustering process to translate individual SV signals into putative SV candidates.",
    "First, SV signals extracted from reads in the pre-processing step are clustered based on their indicated SV type and genomic start position.",
    "Second, insertion and deletion sequences in each cluster stemming from the same read are merged to correct for alignment errors in highly repetitive regions.",
    "Third, preliminary clusters are re-split to represent different supported SV lengths.",
    "The first clustering phase constitutes a fast pass over all bins (default bin size, 100 bp) containing SV signals extracted from alignments in the pre-processing step."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}